Interface ApplicationConsole

public interface ApplicationConsole

An ApplicationConsole provides standard out and err output facilities to an executing application.

printf

void printf(String format,
            Object... args)
A convenience method to write a formatted string to a console using the specified format string and arguments.

Parameters:
format - a format string as described in Formatter string syntax
args - arguments referenced by the format specifiers in the format string. If there are more arguments than format specifiers, the extra arguments are ignored. The number of arguments is variable and may be zero.
